result.execSummary:
The defendant Leonard D Sharlow Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery of a Financial Institution [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.87.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: The restitution amount listed reflects an additional Administrative Cost of 10% of the amount of restitution pursuant to Section 973.06(1)(g).  The 5% Restitution Surcharge is equal to 5% of the total of the restitution, costs, attorney fees, and fines, pursuant to Section 973.20(11)(a).

Fines, costs, and restitution are due during term of supervision.  Court further orders 25% of prison wages to be applied toward Court-ordered financial obligations.  If defendant is released with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment enforceable by all creditors' remedies shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.

No contact with Alyssa Walker or her family.
No contact with drug users or drug sellers.
No contact with US Bank.
Court orders absolute sobriety.  No possession/consumption of any intoxicants.
Not to possess or consume controlled substances or prescription medication w/out a valid prescription. Not to possess drug paraphernalia.

Defendant to submit to random testing.
Maintain fulltime employment.
Cooperate with programming/treatment deemed appropriate by agent, including AODA, CGIP and mental health.
